Subject: [PATCH] stdlib/private/StdlibUnittestFoundationExtras: restrict to
 Apple platforms

swiftStdlibUnittestFoundationExtras imports ObjectiveC (via
UnavailableFoundationMethodThunks.mm and its Darwin-only
Foundation/Observation SWIFT_MODULE_DEPENDS_* lists a few lines above) —
genuinely Apple-only content, but the add_swift_target_library call had no
TARGET_SDKS restriction saying so. When cross-compiling the standard
library to Android (or any other non-Apple SDK) from this same build, it
was attempted anyway and failed to import ObjectiveC. Restrict it to
ALL_APPLE_PLATFORMS, matching what its own dependency lists already imply.

This patch is a candidate for filing upstream.

Sentinel: NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_ANDROID_STDLIB_UNITTEST_FOUNDATION_EXTRAS

diff --git a/stdlib/private/StdlibUnittestFoundationExtras/CMakeLists.txt b/stdlib/private/StdlibUnittestFoundationExtras/CMakeLists.txt
index ffcb3259043..1b7ffc3c585 100644
--- a/stdlib/private/StdlibUnittestFoundationExtras/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/stdlib/private/StdlibUnittestFoundationExtras/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -18,6 +18,12 @@ add_swift_target_library(swiftStdlibUnittestFoundationExtras ${SWIFT_STDLIB_LIBR
   SWIFT_MODULE_DEPENDS_MACCATALYST ${swift_stdlib_unittest_foundationextras_darwin_dependencies}
   SWIFT_MODULE_DEPENDS StdlibUnittest
   SWIFT_COMPILE_FLAGS ${SWIFT_STANDARD_LIBRARY_SWIFT_FLAGS}
+  # This module imports ObjectiveC (via UnavailableFoundationMethodThunks.mm
+  # and the Darwin-only Foundation/Observation deps above) — genuinely
+  # Apple-only content with no TARGET_SDKS restriction to say so, so it was
+  # being attempted (and failing to import ObjectiveC) when cross-compiling
+  # to Android too.
+  TARGET_SDKS ALL_APPLE_PLATFORMS
   INSTALL_IN_COMPONENT stdlib-experimental
   DARWIN_INSTALL_NAME_DIR "${SWIFT_DARWIN_STDLIB_PRIVATE_INSTALL_NAME_DIR}"

